Late last night, 19 February, a great many Krugersdorp residents were frightened awake by the sound of three powerful explosions, Krugersdorp News reports.
It is alleged that these explosions were the result of an ATM bombing, which occurred in the Nobela Centre in Munsieville, close to Robert Broom Drive in Krugersdorp.
READ MORE:Â ATM bombers strike Reiger Park again
The explosions could be heard throughout the West Rand, from Krugersdorp through to Rangeview, Boltonia, Oatlands, Tarlton, Monument and Kenmare.
No injuries were reported and no known arrests were made. Local police were on scene to investigate the matter.
